    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>The Thunder Bay River Boom Company was formed in 1868 by a group of investors eager to exploit the timber riches surrounding the area of Alpena, Michigan. Its purpose was to control the logging and millwork that was done on the Thunder Bay River, and to separate the logs of the various companies. In 1898, the company was re-established as the Thunder Bay Boom Company.  In 1911, the assets of the company were sold.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The record group consists of financial records, time books of company employees, and articles of incorporation and minutes of stockholders.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <relatedmaterial>
      <p>The researcher should also consult the papers of the Fletcher Family which contains business correspondence relating to their involvement in the company.</p>
    </relatedmaterial>
